Without any prevention measures, the disease would spread all over the world within three months (Fig. 6
). It can be attributed to the convenient and fast movement of human beings. In Fig. 7
(a), the red line describes the diseases which are infectious in both latent period and invasion period, while the orange line depicts diseases which are infectious only in latent period. Making a comparison, the former is over 7.14% than the latter. After analyzing, we summarize two reasons to express the weak distinction: firstly, most neighboring nodes have been infected and the space of infection becomes smaller in invasion period; secondly, the high isolation rate reduces the number of infectors. The green line in Fig. 7(b) represents the number of infectors while taking preventive measures. Compare to the previous red line, number of infectors decreases over 68.7%.
